dct_description_sm: Printed with vegetation. Prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (AM), Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army , original map compiled by USGS. Variant title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Maywood, Indiana. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V851 Sheet 3763 II NW. AMS 1. Transverse Mercator projection. "A.M.S. Series V851" Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, schools, churches, cemeteries, mines, and natural features. "Transverse Mercator projection." "Contour interval 10 feet." Marginal maps: Index to boundaries.--Index to adjoining sheets. "Scale changed, marginal data revised and Universal Transverse Mercator Grid added, 1948. Copied in 1948 from Indiana, 1:24,000, USGS, Maywood, 1947. Original map compiled by USGS 1947, from planetable surveys and stereophotogrammetric methods, 1946. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC & GS. ... Map field checked." "N3937.5-W8607.5/7.5." "AMS 1, 1948." "2-49."
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, 1948.
Dimensions: 56 x 45 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:25,000
dct_creator_sm: Geological Survey (U.S.); United States. Army Map Service
